text: Survivor Series (2010) was a professional wrestling pay-per-view show made by World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE). It took place on November 21, 2010 at the American Airlines Arena in Miami, Florida. It was the 24th Survivor Series event held by WWE. Eight matches were contested at the event. In the main event, Randy Orton defeated Wade Barrett to retain the WWE Championship with John Cena as the special guest referee. Since Orton won, Cena was (kayfabe) fired from WWE. ==Matches== No. Results Stipulations Times 1 R-Truth (with Eve Torres) defeated Zack Ryder Singles match N/A 2 Daniel Bryan (c) defeated Ted DiBiase
